row.entry:
Concentrated overload
resulting from peening or the pressure of chips between loaded surface;
striking of part with dull object.

Rubbing of two surfaces without sufficient lubrication;
presence of grit between surfaces under pressure during assembly;
unbroken edges of press fitted parts; incipient seizure of rotating
parts during operations.

Deep scratches
made by sharp edges of foreign particles during engine operation;
elongated gouges.

procedure.step:
Benches on which engine parts are placed must be clean and free
from grit, metal filings, etc., which may contaminate engine oil systems,
fuel systems or hardware.
